On Thursday, cops pounced five men on an alleged kidnapping syndicate at a house in Kliprivier. The intelligence-driven raid was led by the South African Police Service and the Directorate for Priority Crimes Investigation (Hawks). According to Brigadier Vishnu Naidoo, the police were following leads on the kidnapping of an Indian National earlier who was kidnapped earlier this month. “This intelligence-led the integrated multi-disciplinary team to the Klipriveir house where a total of five men, two of which are of foreign nationality, were arrested. “Three of these men are likely to be charged with kidnapping while the other two, possibly for unlawful possession of firearms and ammunition,” Brigadier Naidoo said. ALSO READ: ENTIRE NURSING SCHOOL’S TOP TEAM INFECTED! He said foreign military uniform, several firearms including rifles and pistols were recovered in the property. “Some of the long guns include two AK 47 rifles, one Uzzi submachine gun, and two pump-action shotguns. The owner of the house is currently on the run and the kidnapped victim has not yet been found. “In the meantime, we are also investigating the possibility that this group may also be linked to Melville drive-by shooting on New Year’s Day this year,” Brigadier Naidoo added. National Commissioner of the SAPS, General Khehla Sitole praised the police on the arrest. "We must continue with our efforts to trace and arrest the owner of the house and anybody else linked to this group, but more importantly we must find and reunite the kidnapped victim safely with his family", added General Sitole.